apidly during its first ten years, averaging about 7 centimetres per year. After that, its growth slows down to around 4 centimetres per year and over its lifespan, it can reach up to 15 metres. Their long, messy and rough appearance resembles the look of a beard, adding to the tree\u0027s unique and rugged charm.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.JoshuaStars_ROW3275604070_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.JoshuaStars_ROW3275604070_1920x1200.jpg\u0026rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Joshua trees under the Milky Way, California, United States","Copyright":"© Chao Zhang/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz\u0026filters=WQOskey:\u0022HPQuiz_20250421_JoshuaStars\u0022\u0026FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Joshua+tree\u0026form=hpcapt\u0026filters=HpDate:\u002220250421_0700\u0022","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20250421_JoshuaStars"},"AudioContent":null,"VideoContent":null,"Ssd":"20250421_0700","FullDateString":"21 Apr, 2025"}],"preloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Did you know that the first beach chairs were developed in the 19th century to protect against the fine sand and wind? Beach chairs have a special charm even in stormy weather, as in the picture today in front of the pier on Steinwarder in Heiligenhafen, Germany. Steinwarder, a picturesque peninsula, was originally only connected to the mainland by salt marshes and the Eichholz lowlands. Today, it is a paradise for vacationers seeking peace and nature.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BeachChairsSteinwarder_ROW3560286476_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BeachChairsSteinwarder_ROW3560286476_1920x1200.jpg\u0026rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Beach chairs on Steinwarder in Heiligenhafen, Schleswig-Holstein, Germany","Copyright":"© Frank Lukasseck/eStock Photo","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":""